### ── 2. Inspeccionar claims del token ─────────────────────
GET http://localhost:8080/auth/token-info
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### ── 3. Listar todos los blueprints (scope: blueprints.read) ─────────────────
GET http://localhost:8080/api/blueprints
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### ── 4. Obtener blueprint por ID (scope: blueprints.read) ───────────────────
GET http://localhost:8080/api/blueprints/b1
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### ── 5. Obtener blueprints por autor (scope: blueprints.read) ───────────────
GET http://localhost:8080/api/blueprints/author/student
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### ── 6. Crear blueprint (scope: blueprints.write) ───────────────────────────
POST http://localhost:8080/api/blueprints
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Plano nuevo",
  "author": "student"
}

### ── 7. Actualizar blueprint (scope: blueprints.write) ──────────────────────
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/blueprints/b1
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Casa de campo (actualizada)"
}

### ── 8. Eliminar blueprint (scope: blueprints.write) ────────────────────────
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/blueprints/b2
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### ── 9. Sin token → debe retornar 401 ───────────────────────────────────────
GET http://localhost:8080/api/blueprints
